description: My place is a very bright and open studio on the Upper East Side. Between 2nd and 3rd Ave. on 83rd St. this apartment is perfect for a couple or two friends looking for a peaceful place to stay. You are near public transportation, the brand new 2nd avenue subway has just opened in 2017 and walking distance from restaurants, bars, shops, movie theaters, The Metropolitan Museum of Art, The Guggenheim, many other museums and Central Park.

hosts.about: I am a New York resident for over 10 years and have my own photography business. I’m often between my office located one block away from the Airy Townhouse on Upper East Side. I am very personable and love meeting new people.

My name is Isabelle I've  lived in NYC my whole life I love to take pictures and paint and be at the beach. I am an assistant photographer to Lina Jang. I manage her studio apartment on the upper east side.

house_rules:
• Check in is anytime after 3PM
• May not be safe or suitable for children (0-12 years)
• No parties or events
• Not suitable for pets
• No smoking

- After 11 pm be courteous of neighbors
